ght cells","Hollow sphere of 64 cells","Two-cell structure","Fluid-filled cavity with inner cell mass"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAt day four of development, the embryo exists as a \u003Cstrong\u003Esolid ball of 16-32 cells\u003C/strong\u003E called a morula. This structure forms via compaction, where cells develop tight junctions and closely pack together.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent other stages of early development:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETwo-cell structure\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around day two.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESingle layer of eight cells\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around day three before compaction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHollow sphere of 64 cells\u003C/strong\u003E describes the blastocyst stage at day five.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFluid-filled cavity with inner cell mass\u003C/strong\u003E describes the late blastocyst stage\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A morula forms around day four of embryonic development and consists of 16-32 cells in a solid ball arrangement.","Compaction occurs at the eight-cell stage, leading to the formation of the morula through tight junctions between cells."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57054"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15856"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57054","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57054"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T13:30:15+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-19T13:31:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"854